'''Hayde Gofai''' was a [[Human/Legends|Human]] [[Gender/Legends|female]] club-hopper [[Coruscanti/Legends|from]] the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]]. In [[22 BBY/Legends|22 BBY]], she talked with the fellow Human [[Sne Wo]] at the [[Outlander Club/Legends|Outlander Club]] on Coruscant as the [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] [[Obi-Wan Kenobi/Legends|Obi-Wan Kenobi]] and [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Anakin Skywalker]] entered, searching for [[Bounty hunter/Legends|bounty hunter]] [[Zam Wesell/Legends|Zam Wesell]]. She looked for a date in the Skywalker, fixing a bold gaze to him, but unfortunately for her, he was looking for Wesell and not romance.

==Biography==
Hayde Gofai was a [[Human/Legends|Human]] [[Gender/Legends|female]] thrill-seeking club-hopper [[Homeworld/Legends|native]] [[Coruscanti/Legends|to]]<ref name="DB" /> the [[Planet/Legends|planet]]<ref name="TVD">''[[Star Wars: Attack of the Clones: The Visual Dictionary]]''</ref> [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]].<ref name="DB" /> She<ref name="Insider" /> was a participator in Coruscant's party scene.<ref name="Rogues Gallery2">{{InsiderCite|136|Rogues Gallery|Rogues Gallery: A Night at the Outlander Club}}</ref> In [[22 BBY/Legends|22 BBY]],<ref name="NEC">''[[The New Essential Chronology]]'' dates the events of {{Film|II}} to [[22 BBY/Legends|22 BBY]].</ref> Gofai visited the [[Outlander Club/Legends|Outlander Club]],<ref name="EpII" /> a [[Nightclub/Legends|nightclub]] and [[Gambling/Legends|gambling]] hall in the [[Uscru Entertainment District/Legends|Uscru Entertainment District]] of Coruscant.<ref name="CSWE">{{CSWECite|II|431|Outlander Club}}</ref> She walked in the club, drinks in hand, with the fellow Human<ref name="EpII" /> [[Sne Wo]]<ref name="Insider" /> as the [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] [[Padawan/Legends|Padawan]] [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Anakin Skywalker]] and his master [[Obi-Wan Kenobi/Legends|Obi-Wan Kenobi]] entered, [[Plot to assassinate Senator Amidala/Legends|searching]] for the [[Bounty hunter/Legends|bounty hunter]] [[Zam Wesell/Legends|Zam Wesell]]<ref name="EpII" /> 

The pair stood near the entrance of the club as she looked at the Padawan.<ref name="EpII" /> Gofai could not help but notice Skywalker as he surveyed the crowd in the club.<ref name="IntriguedExtras">{{SWArchive|url=episode-ii/explore/attack/2003/05/imageattack20030529.html|series=Image Attack|text=Intrigued Extras}}</ref> Elsewhere in the club, she chatted with Wo<ref name="EpII" /> before trying her luck with Skywalker.<ref name="FF96">{{FactFile|96|OUT 1-2|Outlander Nightclub Patrons}}</ref> She affixed a bold, seductive gaze<ref name="Insider" /> to him as he passed by.<ref name="FF96" /> Unfortunately for her, he was looking for Wesell and not a date.<ref name="Insider" /> 

==Personality and traits==
The club-hopper was a thrill seeker<ref name="DB" /> who was not shy.<ref name="Insider" /> Gofai, who was considered beautiful,<ref name="Insider" /> had [[Color/Legends|brown]] [[Eye/Legends|eye]]<nowiki/>s,<ref name="EpII" /> light skin and blonde hair.<ref name="DB" /> Her feminine first name and her surname were of Human origin.<ref name="GalacticCampaign">''[[Galactic Campaign Guide]]''</ref> She was romantically interested in Anakin Skywalker.<ref name="Insider" />

==Equipment==
At the club, she wore a small black [[Clothing/Legends|top]], small black shorts, a sleeveless blue cloak,<ref name="Rogues Gallery2" /> blue lipstick,<ref name="DepthCommentary">{{HomeVideoCite|film=2|featurette=Depth Commentary}}</ref> black heels, and small stars on her face and body.<ref name="Rogues Gallery2" />

==Behind the scenes==
[[File:HaydeGofai-AOTC1.png|thumb|right|300px|Hayde Gofai first appeared in ''Star Wars: Episode II — Attack of the Clones'' 1.]]
Hayde Gofai was created for the [[prequel trilogy]] film [[Star Wars: Episode II Attack of the Clones|''Star Wars'': Episode II ''Attack of the Clones'']],<ref name="EpII" /> which was released on [[May 16]], [[2002]].<ref name="Year">''[[Star Wars Year by Year: A Visual Chronicle]]''</ref> The Outlander Club scenes including Gofai, who was portrayed by an uncredited<ref name="EpII" /> [[Fiona Johnson]],<ref name="Fiona Johnson">{{WebCite|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/films/news/star-wars-attack-of-the-clones-hid-an-incredibly-subtle-the-matrix-easter-egg-a6735831.html|text=Star Wars: Attack Of The Clones hid an incredibly subtle The Matrix Easter egg|archivedate=20250316054713}}</ref> were shot at [[Fox Studios, Sydney]] on [[July 17]], [[2000]].<ref name="Mythmaking">''[[Mythmaking: Behind the Scenes of Attack of the Clones]]''</ref> The extra introduced the first episode of the Episode II behind-the-scenes video series [[On location|''on location'']],<ref name="On location 1">{{SWArchive|url=episode-ii/bts/onloc/1.html|series=On location|text=Part 1 - Production Offices}}</ref> and then the eighth episode alongside the extra playing Sne Wo and another extra.<ref name="On location 8">{{SWArchive|url=episode-ii/bts/onloc/8.html|series=On location|text=Part 8 - George Lucas in Lunch}}</ref> The first episode, "Production Offices", was released on [[August 1]], 2000.<ref name="Archive">{{SWArchive|url=episode-ii/bts/onloc/archive.html|text=''on location'' archive}}</ref> 

The character first appeared in the [[Star Wars: Episode II — Attack of the Clones 1|first issue]] of the ''[[Star Wars: Episode II — Attack of the Clones (comic series)|Star Wars: Episode II — Attack of the Clones]]'' comic series, penciled by [[Jan Duursema]] and published by [[Dark Horse Comics]]<ref name="AOTCComic">[[Star Wars: Episode II — Attack of the Clones 1|''Star Wars: Episode II — Attack of the Clones'' 1]]</ref> and released on [[April 17]], 2002.<ref name="Date">{{DarkHorse|url=Comics/00-468/Star-Wars-Episode-II----Attack-of-the-Clones-1|text=Star Wars: Episode II -- Attack of the Clones #1}}</ref> Gofai was incorrectly portrayed with dark hair in the comic.<ref name="AOTCComic" /> The character was first identified in an Episode II [[Depth Commentary]] available on [[StarWars.com]] that could be accessed through the DVD-ROM home release of ''Attack of the Clones''<ref name="DepthCommentary" /> on [[November 12]], 2002.<ref name="DVD">{{SWArchive|url=episode-ii/news/2002/08/news20020801.html|text=Episode II On DVD & VHS}}</ref>

